: "طَمَسْنا", "in_corpus": false, "count": null, "asp": "p", "per": "1", "gen": "m", "num": "p"}, {"role": "past_1ms", "form": "طَمَسْتُ", "in_corpus": true, "count": 1, "asp": "p", "per": "1", "gen": "m", "num": "s"}], "frequency_in_corpus": 4, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 4, "pos_tags": ["noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 5}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n27104"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%8E"}}, "translations": {"en": "to obliterate", "fa": "محو کردن", "ur": "محو کرنا", "tr": "silmek", "id": "menghapus", "bn": "মুছে ফেলা", "es": "borrar", "fr": "effacer", "de": "löschen", "ru": "стереть", "zh": "抹去"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to obliterate, to blur, to mask, to efface", "examples": [{"text": "وَقَالَ مُوسَىٰ رَبَّنَا إِنَّكَ آتَيْتَ فِرْعَوْنَ وَمَلَأَهُ زِينَةً وَأَمْوَالًا فِي الْحَيَاةِ الدُّنْيَا رَبَّنَا لِيُضِلُّوٱ عَن سَبِيلِكَ رَبَّنَا ٱطْمِسْ عَلَى أَمْوَالِهِمْ وَٱشْدُدْ عَلَى قُلُوبِهِمْ فَلَا يُؤْمِنُوا حَتَّى يَرَوُٱ الْعَذَابَ الْأَلِيمَ", "english": "And Moses said: Our Lord, verily you have given the Pharaoh and his grandees great shine and wealth in the worldly life, our Lord, that they may lead astray from Your way. Our Lord, obliterate their wealth and harden their hearts so that they will not believe until they see the painful punishment."}]}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to blind", "examples": [{"text": "وَلَوْ نَشَاءُ لَطَمَسْنَا عَلَىٰ أَعْيُنِهِمْ فَٱسْتَبَقُوا الصِّرَاطَ فَأَنَّىٰ يُبْصِرُونَ", "english": "And if we willed, we would blind their eyes, and they would race for the path and how would they see it?"}]}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to become obliterated, to get blurred, to be masked, to be effaced"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to blind"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of طَمَسَ (ṭamasa) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n27104", "headword_ar": "طَمَسَ", "root": "Tms", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M, Msb, K) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TumuwsN", "text_ar": "طُمُوسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, A, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TamosN", "text_ar": "طَمْسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Zj;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a thing, as, for instance, a road, or path, T, S, M, Msb, and a writing, T, or a relic, trace, or vestige, A)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became effaced,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "obliterated;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, M, A, Msb, K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the trace,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mark, thereof"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(i. e. of a road &c.)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became effaced,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "obliterated:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a thing)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "quitted,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "went from, its form,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "shape:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Zj:) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AnTms", "text_ar": "انطمس", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(said of a relic, or remain, or of a mark, or trace, and of a writing, TA, or other thing, S) has the first of the significations above; (S, A, K;) and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tTm~s", "text_ar": "تطمّس", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, K.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "((assumed tropical:)  a star, T, M, and (assumed tropical:)  the moon, and the sight, or eye, M)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lost,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became deprived of, its light."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, M.) [See also the pass. form in what follows.] ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tumuwsu Alqalobi", "text_ar": "طُمُوسُ القَلْبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The heart's becoming in a bad,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "corrupt, state."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O. [See also the last sentence of this paragraph.]) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tamasa Alr~ajulu", "text_ar": "طَمَسَ الرَّجُلُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The man was,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became, distant,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "remote;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "went to a distance,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "far away."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, M, O, K.) ―         -b5-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tamasa", "text_ar": "طَمَسَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biEayonihi", "text_ar": "بِعَيْنِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, O, K,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TamosN", "text_ar": "طَمْسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (IDrd, O,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He looked far:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, O, K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he looked at a thing from afar."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IDrd, O.)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tamasahu", "text_ar": "طَمَسَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, IKtt, Msb, K,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tamasa Ealayohi", "text_ar": "طَمَسَ عَلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, TA,) aor."}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, Msb,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TamosN", "text_ar": "طَمْسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He effaced it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "obliterated it;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, Msb, K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he effaced,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "obliterated,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "removed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "extirpated,"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1881}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the trace,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mark, thereof;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K, TA;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tm~shu", "text_ar": "طمّسهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, TA,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "taTomiysN", "text_ar": "تَطْمِيسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he destroyed it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IKtt:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tamasa Almakotuwba", "text_ar": "طَمَسَ المَكْتُوبَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also expl. as signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he covered the writing by folding."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Har p. 505.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tamasatohu Alr~iyHu", "text_ar": "طَمَسَتْهُ الرِّيحُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The wind effaced,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "obliterated, it;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "namely, the trace, or mark, of a thing. (A.) And it is said in the Kur [lxxvii. 8],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA_i*aA Aln~ujuwmu Tumisato", "text_ar": "فَاـِذَا النُّجُومُ طُمِسَتْ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And when the stars shall have their traces extirpated:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "shall lose their light."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, TA.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tamasa A^aEoyunahumo", "text_ar": "طَمَسَ اَعْيُنَهُمْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [as in the Kur liv. 37,] (A,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY A^aEoyunihimo", "text_ar": "عَلَى اَعْيُنِهِمْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (T, A,) as in the Kur xxxvi. 66, (T,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(God)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "blinded them."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence, app.,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tamasa Algayomu", "text_ar": "طَمَسَ الغَيْمُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~ujuwma", "text_ar": "النُّجُومَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The clouds,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mist, covered,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "concealed, the stars;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as though it put out their light]. (A.) ―         -b4-  And [hence also,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tamasa", "text_ar": "طَمَسَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (O, K,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TamaAsapN", "text_ar": "طَمَاسَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (O, * K, * TK,) (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He conjectured,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "computed by conjecture,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, K, TA, TK,) a thing: (TK:) because the doing so is generally accompanied by the putting of the eyelids together, as though one were blinded. (TA.) ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tamasahu", "text_ar": "طَمَسَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TamosN", "text_ar": "طَمْسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", also signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(God)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "transformed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "metamorphosed, him"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) Hence the saying in the Kur [x. 88],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rab~anaA A@Tomiso EalaY A^amowaAlihimN", "text_ar": "رَبَّنَا ا@طْمِسْ عَلَى اَمْوَالِهِمٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "O our Lord, transform their possessions:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) they say that they became stones: (O, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "change,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "alter, their possessions:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "destroy their possessions:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ibn-Arafeh, O, Bd, K:) the verb is also read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@Tomuso", "text_ar": "ا@طْمُسْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Bd.) This"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tamos", "text_ar": "طَمْس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "was the last of the nine signs which were given to Moses, when the property of Pharaoh was transformed at his prayer, and became stones. (M.) [See the Kur xvii. 103, and xxvii. 12.] In like manner, it is said in the Kur [iv. 50],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino qaboli A^ano naTomisa wujuwhFA", "text_ar": "مِنْ قَبْلِ اَنْ نَطْمِسَ وُجُوهًا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Before we change,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "alter, faces:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S:) or these words, with what immediately follows,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fanarud~ahaA EalaY A^adobaArihaA", "text_ar": "فَنَرُدَّهَا عَلَى اَدْبَارِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", are expl. in three different ways:"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "before we make faces to be like the backs of necks:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "before we make faces to be places in which hair shall grow like the backs of necks:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "before we make them to err,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in requital of their opposition. (Zj, TA.) ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TamosN", "text_ar": "طَمْسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fasaAdN", "text_ar": "فَسَادٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as though in the sense of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ifosaAdN", "text_ar": "اـِفْسَادٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "making,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rendering, bad, corrupt,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.: but see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tumuwsu Alqalobi", "text_ar": "طُمُوسُ القَلْبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", above]. (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "M", "Msb", "K", "A", "Zj", "O", "IDrd", "IKtt", "TA", "T", "God", "TK"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}